SIMPLE: shaver
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shaver
<hw>Shav"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
shaves; one whose occupation is to shave.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who is close in bargains; a sharper.</def>
<rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who fleeces; a pillager; a plunderer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By these <qex>shavers</qex> the Turks were stripped.</q>
<rj><qau>Knolles.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A boy; a lad; a little fellow.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧These unlucky little
<xex>shavers</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <-- often little shaver -->
<rj><au>Salmagundi.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As I have mentioned at the door to this young <qex>shaver</qex>, I
am on a chase in the name of the king.</q>
<rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>A tool or machine for
shaving.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>A note shaver</b></col>, <cd>a person who buys notes at a
discount greater than the legal rate of interest.</cd> <mark>[Cant,
U.S.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shaving</ent>⟦br⟧
